00:02:03.780 --> 00:02:07.140
So the line in the past is a very safe tense.

00:02:07.140 --> 00:02:10.340
We just have a few irregular verbs, but for the rest

00:02:10.560 --> 00:02:20.400
We can be very certain that taking off the R and putting abba or taking off the RIR and putting I is going to give us the result that we want.

00:02:20.379 --> 00:02:26.780
The point in the past is less regular, less reliable.

00:02:26.780 --> 00:02:32.140
There are a group of verbs in the dot or the point in the past

00:02:32.320 --> 00:02:37.120
Which are irregular but they all do something very similar.

00:02:37.120 --> 00:02:41.200
Now most of the verbs in this group are got verbs

00:02:41.220 --> 00:02:42.739
But not all of them.

00:02:42.739 --> 00:02:51.379
Now, what these verbs do in the point in the past is that firstly the beginning bit of the verb.

00:02:51.379 --> 00:02:53.620
So for example, if we have poder

00:02:54.820 --> 00:02:57.860
That beginning bit pod changes.

00:02:57.860 --> 00:02:59.300
And we already saw this.

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:03.780
We saw, for example, they were able was pudieron.

00:03:03.780 --> 00:03:06.340
So that pod changes to pod.

00:03:06.140 --> 00:03:11.420
Here it's a little change, but there are more drastic changes with other verbs.

00:03:11.420 --> 00:03:13.019
So this is the first thing.

00:03:13.019 --> 00:03:17.819
The base of the verb that is left once we take the endings off changes

00:03:17.640 --> 00:03:22.599
Sometimes radically, sometimes a little bit like here from pod to pud.

00:03:22.599 --> 00:03:25.799
The second thing that they do is that they use

00:03:26.580 --> 00:03:32.660
A mixture of the point endings from R verbs and from R-Er verbs.

00:03:32.660 --> 00:03:37.060
They use a mixture of the two endings from both sides.

00:03:36.980 --> 00:03:41.620
but always the same mixture for each of these irregular verbs.

00:03:41.620 --> 00:03:47.220
And the third thing they do is to not have the accent on the endings.

